cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on image synthesis using deep learning techniques, specifically generative Markov random field (MRF) models and discriminatively trained deep convolutional neural networks (dCNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of MRFs and deep learning for image synthesis, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of MRFs for controlling image layout, which is related to the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper discusses the synthesis of non-photo-realistic (artwork) images, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
